# Kali Linux VM — Attack Machine

## Overview
Deployed Kali Linux as a dedicated attack machine virtual machine within the Proxmox homelab environment. Kali Linux serves as the offensive platform for simulating real-world attacks against target machines in the lab, generating authentic malicious traffic and logs that defensive tools like Splunk can detect and alert on. This mirrors the red team infrastructure commonly referenced in enterprise SOC environments when analyzing attacker behavior.

