## Installation Process

### Step 1 — ISO Preparation
Downloaded the Kali Linux 2024.x x86_64 Installer ISO from kali.org and uploaded directly to the Proxmox local storage pool via the ISO Images interface.

### Step 2 — VM Creation
Created a new VM in Proxmox with the configuration detailed in the table above. Selected VirtIO for both disk and network adapter to ensure optimal performance within the Proxmox virtualization environment.

### Step 3 — OS Installation
Booted the VM from the Kali ISO and proceeded through the graphical installer:
- Selected guided disk partitioning using the full 40GB VirtIO disk
- Configured a dedicated non-root user account for daily use
- Installed the full Kali desktop environment with default tool selection
- Installed GRUB bootloader to /dev/vda

### Step 4 — First Boot Verification
Successfully booted into the Kali Linux desktop environment confirming full graphical interface functionality and tool availability.

